blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

body:
JOHN WICK IMAGINE Part 1

Plot: You and John are enjoying an evening nap when assassins invade the privacy of your home.

Warning: mentions of blood and violence, sexual reference

“Good morning, John,” you greeted.

“Good evening beautiful.” he corrected with a soft smirk.

"Did you enjoy your nap?” You smiled sweetly at him, gently laying your head on the pillow as he moved to lay on his back.

“I did actually.” He sighed.

“Told ya. I knew you needed the nap, you’re exhausted John.”

“I suppose.” He said, face turning towards you. His arm stretched over, cupping your cheek, making you giggle.

The sheets between you two started to move, looking down, you both watched as John’s Dog’s head nudge under John’s arm. You smiled at the cutie and pet his big head.

“John, will you name this cutie pie already.”

“I did, it’s Dog.” He chuckled. You rolled your eyes and smiled at the cutie before curling back over to John.

“Another nap?” He asked, playing with your hair as you laid on his chest. You nodded.

Soon you two were near a deep sleep till a crack of lightning hit. You jumped. Looking around the room, lightning strikes being the only source of light, you saw John’s silhouette sitting up in bed.

“John, what’s wrong?” You asked, getting a little scared. John’s dog started to growl at the door. You started to sit up when John stopped you, putting a hand over your chest.

“Grab the dog. Don’t come out for any reason, I’ll come and get you.”

“John-” you started, nearly whining from fear.

“Go.” He demanded, before getting up and grabbing his gun from under the bed.

You quickly pulled the dog to the bathroom, the dog resisting till John whispered something in German to him, to which the dog obliged and followed you to the bathroom. You locked the door and waited. It was quiet, your heart was racing.

Gun-fire, crashes, thuds and grunting were heard from downstairs. The dog started barking and whining frantically. Tears quickly streamed down your face as your shaken hands tried to quiet the dog.

The storm, the frightening noises from below and simply the rush of it all, overwhelmed you so much so that you weren’t even aware that someone was in the room till they attempted to kick down the bathroom door. You looked around the bathroom, grabbing the heavy hood of the toilet, when the door finally broke down. Before you could react, the dog immediately attacked the man, dragging him out of the bathroom. You followed, till another man pushed you to the ground, knocking your porcelain weapon out of your head, shattering it all over the floor. You squirmed from under him. He grabbed your jaw.

“If we didn’t have to bring you in, I don’t know if I’d kill ya or have my way first.” He hissed over you, gripping your thigh with his other hand. You whined and screamed for John. You peeked over to find the dog but he was nowhere in sight. You tried to push him off, upon doing so you felt a knife on the man’s body. He wrapped his hand around your throat, attempting to knock you out enough so you would black out without killing you. Your other hand struggled to peel his off, while the knife slowly made it’s way into your hand.

“Please…” You stammered.

He laughed. Everything started to grow hazy.

His laughing stopped, blood spilling out of his mouth and onto your face, his eyes now bloodshot. His body grew limp and heavier but your adrenaline helped you to push his body off. The knife was stiff in his stomach, your shaken hands were covered in blood. It was everywhere, all over your bathroom floor, your clothes, hands and face. Quick footsteps were distant, your mind focused on the blood. John grabbed you, moving your face to his. His mouth was moving but you didnt hear what he said.

“It’s not mine. It’s not mine.” You repeated.

He stared at you and gathered that you were talking about the blood. He knew you were in shock, and rightfully so.

“I’m so sorry sweetheart. I - I need to get you somewhere safe before I can take care of you. But i need to know if you’re hurt.” He said. He knew there was definite bruising, cuts and other minor issues, but he quickly scanned your body for severe damage, you were not in any condition to tell him yourself. He scooped you up and walked out of the bathroom, stopping in front of the doorframe of your bedroom. It was dark downstairs, but flashes of lightning illuminated shards of glass and splattered blood on the wood floor.

“I’m gonna need you to close your eyes for me sweetheart.” He spoke softly. You immediately did as told. John continued to walk down the stairs. You heard his footsteps and shards of glass scraping the floor as his foot moved them out of the way.

“John?” You asked, eyes still closed.

“He’s waiting outside.” John answered, knowing your concern of the dog.

You heard the swish of the grass as John made his way over to the car. Opening the door and slowly placing you in.

“It’s okay now. You can open your eyes, it’s safe.” He said, as he climbed into the car himself. You looked over at the dog, panting in the backseat, then over at John. He started the car, and held your hand as he drove off. You were both covered in blood, but you tried to focus your attention on the view outside. Meanwhile, John kept wondering not only whose men they belonged to and why they were there, but why they went after you without killing you.

So! This was my first ever John Wick imagine, I hope you guys enjoyed it, let me know what you think. OH! And let me know if you think there should be a part 2 😉

That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

Idk whether to laugh or cry..

And when I asked him how it was, he just went “meh”.

biTCH, MEH?! MEH?! ARE YOU SERIOUS?!
